<body>
    <h1>Environments</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout two-right-sidebar" data-layout=3D"two-right-side=
bar">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<p>Environment configuration as provided by Symfony is enhanced in eZ Platf=
orm to allow specifying this in the virtual host configuration.<br>You can =
configure several environments, from production, development or staging, ev=
en if for each one of them you need to use different configuration sets.</p=
>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p><span>See also </span><a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/cookbook=
/configuration/environments.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
the Symfony Recipe about " How to Master and Create new Environments "</a><=
/p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"Environments-Webserverconfiguration">Web server configuration</h1=
>
<p>For example, using Apache, in the <code>VirtualHost</code> example in <a=
 href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezplatform/tree/master/doc/apache2" c=
lass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">doc/apache2/</a>&nbsp;in your insta=
ll, the required <code>VirtualHost</code> configurations have been already =
included. You can switch to the desired environment by setting the <code>EN=
VIRONMENT</code> environment variable to "<code>prod</code>", "<code>dev</c=
ode>" or other custom value, as you can see in the following example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: plain; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-si=
ze:12px;"># Environment.
# Possible values: "prod" and "dev" out-of-the-box, other values possible w=
ith proper configuration
# Defaults to "prod" if omitted (uses SetEnvIf so value can be used in rewr=
ite rules)
SetEnvIf Request_URI ".*" SYMFONY_ENV=3D"prod"</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"Environments-Configuration">Configuration</h1>
<p>If you want to use a custom environment (something else then "<code>prod=
</code>" and "<code>dev</code>") the next step is to create the dedicated c=
onfiguration files for your environment:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>app/config/config_<strong> <em>&lt;env_name&gt;</em> </strong>.ym=
l</code></li>
<li><code>app/config/ezplatform_<strong> <em>&lt;env_name&gt;</em> </strong=
>.yml</code></li>
</ul>
<p>The name used as <code> <strong> <em>&lt;env_name&gt;</em> </strong> </c=
ode> will be the one that can be used as value of the <code>ENVIRONMENT</co=
de> environment variable.</p>
<p>Those files must import the main configuration file, just like the defau=
lt&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-community/blob/ma=
ster/ezpublish/config/config_dev.yml" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow"> <code>config_dev.yml</code> </a> already does. Here's an example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">imports:
    - { resource: config.yml }</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>This allows you to override settings defined in the main configuration f=
ile, depending on your environment (like the DB settings or any other setti=
ng you may want to override).</p>
</div>=20
</div>=20
<div class=3D"cell aside" data-type=3D"aside">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
